DLW-SPUN · the full weave of Ulysses

who   : The cunning king of Ithaca — Odysseus.
what  : A false counselor, his soul wrapped in a single tongue of flame.
where : Circle VIII — Fraud, the eighth ditch of Malebolge.
why   : The Trojan Horse, and a lifetime of guile that won and ruined.
when  : He tells of his last mad voyage, past the world's edge, to the drowning mountain.
how   : He speaks from inside the fire, and his words are gold and ruin at once.

